Gross Description
A.  Received fresh labeled ""left lobe biopsy are multiple (2) tan cores (0.5 cm and 0.8 cm in length).  All submitted.  Grossed by EADDY.

B.  Received fresh labeled ""nodule liver segment III"" is a 1.4 x 0.8 x 0.6 cm portion of liver.  All submitted.  Grossed by CALABRO.

C.  Received fresh labeled ""nodule liver segment II"" is a 1.7 x 1.5 x 0.7 cm portion of liver.  There is a 0.2 x 0.2 x 0.2 cm white nodule located 0.2 cm from the margin.  Representative sections are submitted.  Grossed by EADDY.

D.  Received fresh labeled ""nodule liver segment VIII"" is a 3.2 x 2.5 x 1.6 cm portion of liver.  There is a 0.7 x 0.4 x 0.3 cm white nodule located 0.5 cm to the surgical margin.  Representative sections are submitted.  Grossed by CALABRO.

E.  Received fresh labeled ""nodule liver segment V"" is a 3.5 x 2.8 x 1.5 cm aggregate of liver parenchyma.  A 0.4 x 0.3 x 0.3 cm nodule is present.  Representative sections are submitted.  Grossed by CALABRO.

F.  Received fresh labeled ""portion liver segment VII"" is a 45.3 gram, 6.7 x 4.9 x 3.1 cm partial hepatectomy specimen.  A single 2.2 x 2.0 x 1.7 cm mass is present 0.4 cm from the surgical margin.  Representative sections are submitted.  Grossed by EADDY.

G.	Received fresh labeled rectum is a low anterior resection specimen consisting of 28.0 cm in length portion of rectosigmoid colon. A 1.6 x 1.3 x 0.6 cm ulcerative mass is present within the distal margin, 1.2 cm from the mucosal margin, and 0.6 cm from the radial margin. Tumor perforation is absent. Multiple lymph nodes are identified within the perirectal fat. Representative sections are submitted.  Grossed by CALABRO.

H.	Received fresh labeled mucosectomy anal canal is a 4.5 x 2.2 x 0.2 cm aggregate of bowel mucosa.  Representative sections are submitted.  Grossed by CALABRO.





