G.	Rectum, resection:  Adenocarcinoma, moderately differentiated (grade 3 of 4), forming a 1.6 x 1.3 x 0.6 cm ulcerated mass in the rectum.  Tumor invades through the muscularis propria into the pericolic fat.  Lymphatic/vascular invasion is absent.  The tumor extends to within 0.6 cm of the radial resection margin.  The tumor is located 1.2 cm from the distal margin.  Holdover for permanent sections on lymph nodes.

